Botswana Says its Fourth-Quarter Trade Deficit Widens to $326 Million

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-05-06T14:33:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/botswana-says-its-fourth-quarter-trade-deficit-widens-to-326-million.html
Botswana’s trade deficit widened to
2.1 billion pula from 1.2 billion pula ($326 million) in the
third quarter, the country’s statistics agency said.  Exports rose 2.5 percent to 8.44 billion pula while imports
jumped 11 percent to 10.54 billion pula, the agency said.
Diamonds exports, which accounted for 70 percent of all
shipments, rose to 5.88 billion pula from 5.24 billion pula.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  